tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE qubit_states (
  qubit_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  state VARCHAR NOT NULL
)

CREATE TABLE qubit_measurements (
  measurement_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  qubit_id INT NOT NULL,
  measurement_result VARCHAR NOT NULL
)

CREATE TABLE quantum_experiment (
  experiment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  experiment_name VARCHAR NOT NULL,
  start_time TIMESTAMP,
  end_time TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE measurements (
    measurement_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    qubit_id INT,
    measurement_time TIMESTAMP,
    measurement_value FLOAT,
    FOREIGN KEY (qubit_id) REFERENCES qubits(qubit_id)
);

CREATE TABLE simulation_results (
    result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_id INT,
    measurement_id INT,
    result_value FLOAT,
    FOREIGN KEY (experiment_id) REFERENCES experiments(experiment_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (measurement_id) REFERENCES measurements(measurement_id)
);

CREATE TABLE experiment_results (
    result_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_id INT NOT NULL REFERENCES quantum_experiment(experiment_id),
    qubit_id INT NOT NULL REFERENCES qubit_states(qubit_id),
    measurement_id INT NOT NULL REFERENCES qubit_measurements(measurement_id),
    result VARCHAR(10) NOT NULL
);
